## Warning: Removed 1594 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

  1. Setting the color in the aesthetic here does not change the color of the geom_point layer, but it is trying to stratify the data points in the plot by a string, blue in this case, which is why we see the blue in the legend. It would have to go outside of the aes() somewhere.
ggplot(data = NHANES) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = Height, y = Weight, color = "blue"))
